1
00:00:49,720 --> 00:00:51,720
Master Pang has princess syndrome.

2
00:00:52,120 --> 00:00:54,050
Always trying to get my attention.

3
00:00:54,200 --> 00:00:56,440
Every now and then, he takes something

4
00:00:56,880 --> 00:00:58,200
shiny from my table.

5
00:00:59,040 --> 00:01:00,560
I'll let you pick them up.

6
00:01:02,400 --> 00:01:03,680
What about the other pieces?

7
00:01:03,680 --> 00:01:05,519
It's good enough I got this piece back.

8
00:01:05,519 --> 00:01:06,850
The rest can't be found.

9
00:01:42,240 --> 00:01:42,840
Mr. Zhang,

10
00:01:43,720 --> 00:01:44,850
can I say a few words?

11
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:45,800
Wait a minute.

12
00:01:48,039 --> 00:01:48,570
Go ahead.

13
00:01:49,080 --> 00:01:49,880
Dear viewers.

14
00:01:50,640 --> 00:01:52,640
I am a teacher at Jingdezhen Ceramic University,

15
00:01:52,640 --> 00:01:54,360
specializing in restoration.

16
00:01:54,360 --> 00:01:55,490
My name is Yue Qixin.

17
00:01:55,840 --> 00:01:58,600
I take full responsibility for what I am about to say.

18
00:01:58,600 --> 00:01:59,660
Please take a look.

19
00:02:00,360 --> 00:02:02,720
We found this in the shop.

20
00:02:03,040 --> 00:02:04,880
It is a piece of

21
00:02:05,280 --> 00:02:07,320
the porcelain bowl smashed

22
00:02:07,320 --> 00:02:08,520
by Mr. Zhang himself.

23
00:02:08,759 --> 00:02:11,620
There are obvious traces of piecing together here.

24
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:13,480
According to the instrument test,

25
00:02:13,480 --> 00:02:14,140
the old part

26
00:02:14,480 --> 00:02:16,010
is indeed as Mr. Zhang said,

27
00:02:17,040 --> 00:02:20,570
an old bowl bottom from the Chenghua period of the Ming Dynasty.

28
00:02:20,840 --> 00:02:23,320
But the new part is obviously a fake.

29
00:02:24,040 --> 00:02:24,680
This shows

30
00:02:25,079 --> 00:02:28,340
that the porcelain bowl Mr. Zhang smashed was a pieced one.

31
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:31,320
This also proves that what Xu Xiao

32
00:02:32,240 --> 00:02:33,700
said to you two at that time

33
00:02:34,280 --> 00:02:35,240
is correct.

34
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:37,730
Everyone, please look.

35
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:38,720
This

36
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:43,530
is the certificate issued by the Ceramics Research Institute.

37
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:51,600
Mr. Zhang.

38
00:02:52,560 --> 00:02:55,800
It's time for this farce to end.

39
00:02:56,600 --> 00:02:58,640
And from now on,

40
00:02:59,079 --> 00:03:00,320
please stop your slander against Xu Xiao

41
00:03:00,320 --> 00:03:02,380
and Jingdezhen Ceramic University.

42
00:03:02,880 --> 00:03:03,600
Otherwise,

43
00:03:04,160 --> 00:03:07,360
you will face legal sanctions and punishment.

44
00:03:08,440 --> 00:03:09,520
Do you understand?

45
00:03:13,640 --> 00:03:14,640
In most cases,

46
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:18,050
people can only see the world they want to see.

47
00:03:19,040 --> 00:03:21,900
They only believe what they are willing to believe.

48
00:03:22,160 --> 00:03:23,000
Over time,

49
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:25,280
they will fall into a vicious circle,

50
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:27,360
trapping themselves inside, unable to get out.

51
00:03:27,360 --> 00:03:30,160
I don't want to see this kind of thing happen again.

52
00:03:58,840 --> 00:04:00,040
So Xu Xiao's issue

53
00:04:00,040 --> 00:04:01,360
has been completely resolved, right?

54
00:04:01,360 --> 00:04:04,200
I saw Zhang Jiatian apologize in the livestream.

55
00:04:04,480 --> 00:04:05,840
Many buyers are demanding refunds.

56
00:04:05,840 --> 00:04:06,700
He apologized.

57
00:04:06,760 --> 00:04:08,960
Evil people will get their comeuppance.

58
00:04:08,960 --> 00:04:09,490
Exactly.

59
00:04:10,040 --> 00:04:11,360
Here he comes.

60
00:04:17,040 --> 00:04:17,680
Applaud.

61
00:04:20,040 --> 00:04:20,399
Mr. Yue.

62
00:04:20,399 --> 00:04:21,440
As expected of Mr. Yue.

63
00:04:21,440 --> 00:04:22,120
Hello, Mr. Yue.

64
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:23,040
You look so handsome, Mr. Yue.

65
00:04:23,040 --> 00:04:23,360
Great.

66
00:04:23,360 --> 00:04:23,720
So handsome.

67
00:04:23,720 --> 00:04:24,960
Mr. Yue! Mr. Yue!

68
00:04:26,760 --> 00:04:28,290
As expected of you, Mr. Yue.

69
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:30,640
That was so cool!

70
00:04:30,640 --> 00:04:31,640
Mr. Yue is the best.

71
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:32,120
Mr. Yue,

72
00:04:35,680 --> 00:04:36,280
thank you.

73
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:39,440
All right, get up.

74
00:04:40,760 --> 00:04:43,280
The ones you should thank the most are your classmates.

75
00:04:43,280 --> 00:04:44,080
Yes.

76
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:46,130
Another round of applause.

77
00:04:49,159 --> 00:04:49,720
Go back.

78
00:04:50,400 --> 00:04:51,560
Alright, class.

79
00:04:51,840 --> 00:04:52,370
Alright.

80
00:04:52,640 --> 00:04:53,040
Class begins.

81
00:04:53,040 --> 00:04:53,560
Okay.

82
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:05,720
The deceased was at the third-floor bar of the annex.

83
00:05:05,720 --> 00:05:07,840
The door to the third-floor bar opens inward,

84
00:05:07,840 --> 00:05:09,170
and could not be opened.

85
00:05:09,320 --> 00:05:11,120
The windows were also locked from the inside.

86
00:05:11,120 --> 00:05:12,920
So this is a perfect locked room.

87
00:05:13,440 --> 00:05:14,480
The solution to this case,

88
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:16,010
which is the only solution,

89
00:05:16,080 --> 00:05:18,200
is that the killer took advantage of everyone's fixed mindset.

90
00:05:18,200 --> 00:05:21,000
To create the illusion that he had just arrived at the crime scene.

91
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:21,560
In fact,

92
00:05:22,080 --> 00:05:24,360
he had been hiding in the wine cabinet and never left.

93
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:25,240
And among us,

94
00:05:25,640 --> 00:05:28,900
the only one who had the chance to hide in the wine cabinet is

95
00:05:29,200 --> 00:05:29,860
Lin Yuexin.

96
00:05:34,560 --> 00:05:36,480
I think we can just vote for the killer.

97
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:39,210
We don't need to proceed with the rest of the game.

98
00:05:41,560 --> 00:05:43,890
I think we shouldn't invite him next time.

99
00:05:48,480 --> 00:05:50,409
My back hurts from sitting so long.

100
00:05:50,480 --> 00:05:51,640
It can't be helped.

101
00:05:52,400 --> 00:05:54,880
I was found out the first time I was the killer.

102
00:05:54,880 --> 00:05:55,520
Yan Xue.

103
00:05:56,159 --> 00:05:57,159
Wait a moment.

104
00:05:57,880 --> 00:05:58,480
What's up?

105
00:06:03,960 --> 00:06:05,440
I want to give this to you.

106
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:11,720
Xu Xiao and I fixed this together.

107
00:06:12,720 --> 00:06:13,580
My assignment.

108
00:06:14,440 --> 00:06:15,480
About what happened before, I...

109
00:06:15,480 --> 00:06:16,120
I'm sorry.

110
00:06:20,160 --> 00:06:20,800
First,

111
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:23,520
I want to thank you for fixing my porcelain.

112
00:06:23,520 --> 00:06:25,450
Second, I want to apologize to you.

113
00:06:26,400 --> 00:06:27,000
But I hope

114
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:28,860
you can understand why I did that.

115
00:06:28,880 --> 00:06:30,080
I thought you liked Xu Xiao,

116
00:06:30,080 --> 00:06:31,160
but were keeping it a secret on purpose.

117
00:06:31,160 --> 00:06:32,200
That day you said you wouldn't team up with him,

118
00:06:32,200 --> 00:06:33,530
but you did the next day.

119
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:35,040
We all thought you were being two-faced,

120
00:06:35,040 --> 00:06:36,159
so we were very angry.

121
00:06:36,159 --> 00:06:36,920
But after a while,

122
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:38,760
I realized you really didn't know.

123
00:06:38,760 --> 00:06:40,280
So I want to apologize to you.

124
00:06:40,280 --> 00:06:41,010
It's not you.

125
00:06:41,880 --> 00:06:43,159
Can't you just face

126
00:06:43,159 --> 00:06:44,290
your true feelings?

127
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:45,560
I...

128
00:06:45,560 --> 00:06:45,960
Also,

129
00:06:46,440 --> 00:06:48,000
I think Xu Xiao likes you.

130
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:49,480
No, he's just...

131
00:06:49,480 --> 00:06:50,940
If Xu Xiao didn't like you,

132
00:06:51,159 --> 00:06:51,600
think about it,

133
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:53,600
why would he team up with you? Right?

134
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:54,159
So,

135
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:56,720
can you accept my apology?

136
00:06:59,280 --> 00:06:59,840
I can.

137
00:07:00,560 --> 00:07:02,240
Then let's hug.

138
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:03,920
Okay.

139
00:07:09,760 --> 00:07:10,290
Let's go.

140
00:07:10,520 --> 00:07:10,920
Okay.

141
00:07:12,400 --> 00:07:12,930
Let's go.

142
00:07:32,760 --> 00:07:34,360
It's time for your medicine.

143
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:01,210
Here, take this.

144
00:08:02,080 --> 00:08:05,040
Why is there candy every time I take my medicine?

145
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:07,730
I like sweet things.

146
00:08:07,800 --> 00:08:09,600
I usually keep a few in my pocket.

147
00:08:58,280 --> 00:09:00,320
Crazing refers to

148
00:09:00,320 --> 00:09:03,000
a natural cracking phenomenon on the glaze of porcelain.

149
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:05,860
It was originally a flaw in the firing of porcelain.

150
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:08,330
But after people grasped the pattern,

151
00:09:08,440 --> 00:09:10,040
they created crackle glaze.

152
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:12,400
The cracked surface

153
00:09:12,520 --> 00:09:14,960
instead presented a unique beauty.

154
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:17,460
On the journey of life,

155
00:09:17,480 --> 00:09:19,400
there will be many forks.

156
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:22,440
But it is these countless branches

157
00:09:22,840 --> 00:09:24,280
that make us whole.

158
00:10:30,320 --> 00:10:31,320
His excellence

159
00:10:31,640 --> 00:10:33,500
and an inexplicable persistence

160
00:10:35,040 --> 00:10:36,640
are very attractive, right?

161
00:10:38,120 --> 00:10:39,360
Can you face

162
00:10:39,360 --> 00:10:40,560
your true feelings?

163
00:10:46,240 --> 00:10:47,600
Let's give it a name.

164
00:10:48,400 --> 00:10:50,000
Is Xiao Qing okay?

165
00:11:25,640 --> 00:11:27,570
Hello everyone, my name is Xu Xiao.

166
00:11:27,960 --> 00:11:29,090
Nice to meet you all.

167
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:29,800
Thank you.

168
00:11:37,240 --> 00:11:38,440
I'll team up with you.

169
00:11:38,800 --> 00:11:39,560
Is that okay?

170
00:11:45,760 --> 00:11:46,200
Here.

171
00:12:04,760 --> 00:12:08,800
So this is what it feels like to fall for someone.

172
00:12:35,640 --> 00:12:36,080
Mom.

173
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:39,260
Take a seat.

174
00:12:47,440 --> 00:12:48,570
Have some tea first.

175
00:12:50,840 --> 00:12:52,760
Asking me out behind your Uncle Song's back,

176
00:12:52,760 --> 00:12:53,760
not going home,

177
00:12:54,040 --> 00:12:55,170
and having tea here.

178
00:13:02,760 --> 00:13:04,420
Zhang Jiatian's live stream,

179
00:13:04,480 --> 00:13:05,410
did you watch it?

180
00:13:05,960 --> 00:13:06,690
Actually...

181
00:13:06,760 --> 00:13:08,490
I know what you're going to say.

182
00:13:09,480 --> 00:13:10,410
Forget about it.

183
00:13:16,560 --> 00:13:18,760
Actually, I've always understood you.

184
00:13:23,920 --> 00:13:25,380
You don't want me to suffer

185
00:13:26,640 --> 00:13:27,920
or be in this industry.

186
00:13:29,040 --> 00:13:30,600
Because of Dad's past,

187
00:13:31,080 --> 00:13:32,600
you don't want people to look down on me.

188
00:13:32,600 --> 00:13:35,260
You definitely don't want me to follow his path.

189
00:13:35,560 --> 00:13:36,200
But Mom,

190
00:13:37,920 --> 00:13:38,920
I want to tell you,

191
00:13:42,440 --> 00:13:44,500
I will never become someone like him.

192
00:13:46,040 --> 00:13:48,300
And I would never do anything to hurt you.

193
00:13:49,840 --> 00:13:51,970
I will never get addicted to antiques.

194
00:13:54,320 --> 00:13:55,160
Because I know

195
00:13:58,000 --> 00:13:59,520
that would only cause my loved ones

196
00:13:59,520 --> 00:14:00,200
to get hurt.

197
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:03,000
I always remember

198
00:14:03,280 --> 00:14:06,080
when our family was in debt when I was young.

199
00:14:08,280 --> 00:14:10,680
You struggled to support the family alone,

200
00:14:11,720 --> 00:14:13,120
losing so much hair,

201
00:14:13,920 --> 00:14:15,980
and staying awake night after night.

202
00:14:17,840 --> 00:14:19,840
In the end, you would just smile at me

203
00:14:22,040 --> 00:14:23,900
and say everything would be fine.

204
00:14:26,560 --> 00:14:27,820
So I always tell myself

205
00:14:29,560 --> 00:14:31,560
that I will never be a man like my dad.

206
00:14:35,520 --> 00:14:37,850
I will never let you suffer any harm again.

207
00:14:41,840 --> 00:14:42,900
Since I was little,

208
00:14:43,880 --> 00:14:44,920
you raised me.

209
00:14:46,120 --> 00:14:47,200
Even though it was because of Dad

210
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:49,130
that I fell in love with this major,

211
00:14:49,800 --> 00:14:52,130
you are the one who taught me how to be a man.

212
00:14:53,040 --> 00:14:53,440
Mom.

213
00:14:54,560 --> 00:14:55,600
I will study hard

214
00:14:56,800 --> 00:14:58,600
and take everything seriously.

215
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:00,640
Even when facing controversy,

216
00:15:00,640 --> 00:15:02,370
I must keep a clear conscience.

217
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:04,260
You taught me all this.

218
00:15:06,880 --> 00:15:09,120
This is not only my respect for my profession,

219
00:15:09,120 --> 00:15:10,650
but also my respect for you.

220
00:15:12,560 --> 00:15:13,000
So,

221
00:15:14,120 --> 00:15:14,560
Mom.

222
00:15:15,560 --> 00:15:16,820
I hope you can trust me.

223
00:15:19,320 --> 00:15:20,250
I am not like him.

224
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:24,600
I won't make you sad anymore.

225
00:15:42,880 --> 00:15:44,320
The color seems too dark,

226
00:15:44,400 --> 00:15:45,060
doesn't it?

227
00:15:45,120 --> 00:15:45,920
A bit too dark.

228
00:15:46,520 --> 00:15:47,000
No good.

229
00:15:47,760 --> 00:15:48,760
Come look at this.

230
00:15:52,640 --> 00:15:53,600
This one is okay.

231
00:15:53,800 --> 00:15:54,600
The color is nice.

232
00:15:54,600 --> 00:15:56,320
That's trying too hard, sis.

233
00:15:56,920 --> 00:15:58,320
It's not trying too hard.

234
00:15:58,520 --> 00:15:59,520
It shows respect.

235
00:15:59,640 --> 00:16:01,120
Besides, it's basic courtesy,

236
00:16:01,120 --> 00:16:01,650
you know?

237
00:16:02,480 --> 00:16:03,240
It's my first time meeting them.

238
00:16:03,240 --> 00:16:04,760
I don't want to dress like this.

239
00:16:04,760 --> 00:16:06,480
Plus, I have my own clothes.

240
00:16:08,640 --> 00:16:09,900
What's wrong with you?

241
00:16:09,960 --> 00:16:10,760
You've been like this since you were little.

242
00:16:10,760 --> 00:16:12,560
You always do the opposite of what I say.

243
00:16:12,560 --> 00:16:13,000
Let me tell you,

244
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:14,120
you're not a kid anymore.

245
00:16:14,120 --> 00:16:14,680
Behave.

246
00:16:16,160 --> 00:16:17,120
Mom, Aunt.

247
00:16:17,160 --> 00:16:18,220
What are you doing?

248
00:16:18,800 --> 00:16:21,530
I'm going out with your mom to meet someone later.

249
00:16:22,240 --> 00:16:23,240
Are you going out?

250
00:16:23,480 --> 00:16:24,610
Are you heading out?

251
00:16:25,440 --> 00:16:27,120
I made plans to go out with a classmate.

252
00:16:27,120 --> 00:16:28,640
Isn't it the weekend today?

253
00:16:28,640 --> 00:16:30,570
Why are you running outside again?

254
00:16:31,040 --> 00:16:32,400
Xiaocen making friends here

255
00:16:32,400 --> 00:16:33,640
is a good thing, sis.

256
00:16:34,280 --> 00:16:35,480
I'm leaving now, Mom.

257
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:36,800
Wait a minute.

258
00:16:40,920 --> 00:16:42,520
Alright, don't forget to drink it.

259
00:16:42,520 --> 00:16:43,200
Got it.

260
00:16:43,360 --> 00:16:43,800
Go.

261
00:16:43,800 --> 00:16:44,530
Bye, Auntie.

262
00:16:44,680 --> 00:16:45,560
Goodbye.

263
00:16:46,920 --> 00:16:48,160
Be careful on the road.

264
00:16:48,160 --> 00:16:48,880
I know.

265
00:16:50,040 --> 00:16:52,100
She's so old but still makes me worry.

266
00:16:53,920 --> 00:16:54,880
You too.

267
00:16:55,800 --> 00:16:56,760
Still drinking water.

268
00:16:56,760 --> 00:16:57,620
Hurry up and go.

269
00:16:58,160 --> 00:16:58,560
Stop drinking.

270
00:16:58,560 --> 00:16:58,880
Sis.

271
00:16:58,880 --> 00:17:00,480
Hurry, get up, be good.

272
00:17:00,480 --> 00:17:01,400
I don't want to wear those clothes anymore.

273
00:17:01,400 --> 00:17:02,720
Hurry up, stand here.

274
00:17:02,960 --> 00:17:04,960
Come on, listen to me, that's right.

275
00:17:10,960 --> 00:17:12,800
Xiaocen, what are you doing today?

276
00:17:12,800 --> 00:17:14,480
Do you want to visit the Imperial Kiln Museum?

277
00:17:14,480 --> 00:17:15,480
I'm already here.

278
00:17:15,599 --> 00:17:17,119
I'm sorry, Yuexin.

279
00:17:17,680 --> 00:17:19,880
I have to work at the antique shop today.

280
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:22,130
You have to go there on the weekend too?

281
00:17:22,280 --> 00:17:24,010
Yeah, Xu Xiao is at the shop too.

282
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:25,319
I need to help out.

283
00:17:25,839 --> 00:17:27,560
Oh, I see.

284
00:17:27,880 --> 00:17:28,680
Alright then.

285
00:17:28,800 --> 00:17:30,130
That's all for now. Bye.

286
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:35,080
This is a blue and white porcelain vat with cloud and dragon patterns.

287
00:17:35,080 --> 00:17:37,480
It was made in the imperial kiln during the Ming Dynasty.

288
00:17:37,480 --> 00:17:39,000
The piece you see now

289
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:40,680
was restored by later generations.

290
00:17:40,680 --> 00:17:41,480
After the founding of the PRC,

291
00:17:41,480 --> 00:17:43,560
We dug up many fragments of dragon vats,

292
00:17:43,560 --> 00:17:45,480
but only three have been truly restored.

293
00:17:45,480 --> 00:17:46,840
One on display is here.

294
00:17:47,120 --> 00:17:50,050
Another is at the Jingdezhen China Ceramics Museum.

295
00:17:54,640 --> 00:17:55,840
Can you guess

296
00:17:55,840 --> 00:17:57,560
what this dragon vat was used for?

297
00:17:57,560 --> 00:17:58,040
Raising fish.

298
00:17:58,040 --> 00:17:59,000
Storing water.

299
00:17:59,160 --> 00:17:59,720
Raising fish.

300
00:17:59,720 --> 00:18:01,320
Right, for storing water.

301
00:18:06,480 --> 00:18:07,040
Xu Xiao.

302
00:18:14,400 --> 00:18:14,930
Morning.

303
00:18:15,480 --> 00:18:16,010
Morning.

304
00:18:17,840 --> 00:18:18,840
Where is the boss?

305
00:18:19,080 --> 00:18:21,680
The boss usually doesn't come in on Saturdays.

306
00:18:22,240 --> 00:18:23,840
It's just the two of us today.

307
00:18:25,760 --> 00:18:26,560
What's wrong?

308
00:18:27,920 --> 00:18:29,320
It's pretty quiet.

309
00:18:46,040 --> 00:18:46,900
Let me help you.

310
00:18:48,040 --> 00:18:49,560
It's fine. Just do your work.

311
00:18:49,560 --> 00:18:50,240
It's okay.

312
00:18:50,760 --> 00:18:52,880
I don't have much to do today anyway.

313
00:18:53,920 --> 00:18:54,560
Okay.

314
00:19:00,480 --> 00:19:01,480
How is my drawing?

315
00:19:03,160 --> 00:19:04,080
Not bad.

316
00:19:04,640 --> 00:19:05,480
Just not bad?

317
00:19:06,160 --> 00:19:07,160
It's pretty good.

318
00:19:07,560 --> 00:19:08,000
Okay.

319
00:19:14,880 --> 00:19:16,080
Um, Xiaocen.

320
00:19:17,520 --> 00:19:19,800
Willing to shed my blood.

321
00:19:21,160 --> 00:19:21,600
Hello, boss.

322
00:19:21,600 --> 00:19:22,530
You're all here.

323
00:19:24,200 --> 00:19:25,130
Why are you here?

324
00:19:25,960 --> 00:19:27,020
Why can't I be here?

325
00:19:28,160 --> 00:19:30,440
Don't you usually avoid coming to the store on weekends?

326
00:19:30,440 --> 00:19:32,520
I'm a pretty casual person.

327
00:19:35,440 --> 00:19:36,370
How's business?

328
00:19:36,560 --> 00:19:37,290
No business.

329
00:19:38,200 --> 00:19:39,060
That's normal.

330
00:19:45,720 --> 00:19:46,650
Are you two busy?

331
00:19:47,360 --> 00:19:47,800
Busy.

332
00:19:48,280 --> 00:19:48,880
Very busy.

333
00:19:49,680 --> 00:19:51,040
Boss, do you need something?

334
00:19:51,040 --> 00:19:52,360
Come over and have a cup of tea.

335
00:19:52,360 --> 00:19:54,000
Newly arrived Lu'an Guapian.

336
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:54,560
Sure.

337
00:19:57,040 --> 00:19:57,840
What's wrong?

338
00:19:59,720 --> 00:20:00,640
When the boss says to drink tea,

339
00:20:00,640 --> 00:20:01,640
it means he wants to chat.

340
00:20:01,640 --> 00:20:03,160
Isn't chatting nice?

341
00:20:05,520 --> 00:20:06,780
You'll find out later.

342
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:07,930
Let's go.

343
00:20:09,960 --> 00:20:11,560
Do you know why I like

344
00:20:11,560 --> 00:20:13,220
hiring you college students?

345
00:20:15,400 --> 00:20:16,160
Because you are

346
00:20:16,160 --> 00:20:17,640
full of youthful energy.

347
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:18,520
Being with you guys

348
00:20:18,520 --> 00:20:19,980
makes me feel young again.

349
00:20:20,440 --> 00:20:22,100
College life is really great.

350
00:20:22,160 --> 00:20:23,120
I still remember

351
00:20:23,120 --> 00:20:24,440
the five guys in my college dorm.

352
00:20:24,440 --> 00:20:26,440
Those five were hidden talents.

353
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:29,400
The guy in the bed diagonally opposite mine

354
00:20:29,400 --> 00:20:30,800
had an incredibly big head.

355
00:20:30,800 --> 00:20:31,640
When it rained,

356
00:20:31,640 --> 00:20:33,200
his clothes never got wet.

357
00:20:33,560 --> 00:20:35,160
His head caught all the rain.

358
00:20:36,640 --> 00:20:38,120
The guy in the bed diagonally opposite on this side

359
00:20:38,120 --> 00:20:39,000
was extremely handsome.

360
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:40,280
The most handsome in our class.

361
00:20:40,280 --> 00:20:42,680
He looked exactly like a young Cai Guoqing.

362
00:20:42,800 --> 00:20:44,260
We all called him Big Eyes.

363
00:20:44,520 --> 00:20:45,840
The guy sleeping head-to-head with me

364
00:20:45,840 --> 00:20:46,560
was smart since he was a kid.

365
00:20:46,560 --> 00:20:47,480
He'd been tricking me since we were young.

366
00:20:47,480 --> 00:20:48,320
Back then, he told me

367
00:20:48,320 --> 00:20:49,040
that in his hometown,

368
00:20:49,040 --> 00:20:49,760
with one whistle,

369
00:20:49,760 --> 00:20:51,560
he could summon twenty big guys.

370
00:20:51,880 --> 00:20:53,480
And I actually believed him, you know?

371
00:20:53,480 --> 00:20:54,120
Later on,

372
00:20:54,880 --> 00:20:56,400
he got into Berklee College of Music.

373
00:20:56,400 --> 00:20:58,130
Became an excellent musician.

374
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:00,240
The most capable and intelligent one

375
00:21:00,240 --> 00:21:02,400
is the one sleeping in the bed opposite mine.

376
00:21:02,400 --> 00:21:05,280
He was among the first batch of live-streamers for e-commerce.

377
00:21:05,280 --> 00:21:07,240
Now he is making a fortune.

378
00:21:07,880 --> 00:21:09,400
He earns a lot of money every day,

379
00:21:09,400 --> 00:21:11,280
and has more than 20 live-streamers working under him.

380
00:21:11,280 --> 00:21:12,280
Isn't he amazing?

381
00:21:14,120 --> 00:21:16,400
Our dorm building is also very beautiful.

382
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:18,920
The whole dorm building is covered with ivy.

383
00:21:19,640 --> 00:21:21,760
The creepers don't dissipate heat.

384
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:22,920
When summer comes,

385
00:21:22,920 --> 00:21:24,360
it becomes unbearably hot.

386
00:21:24,360 --> 00:21:26,040
They cover the whole window completely.

387
00:21:26,040 --> 00:21:27,720
You have to use scissors

388
00:21:27,720 --> 00:21:28,640
to cut them down one by one.

389
00:21:28,640 --> 00:21:30,440
Otherwise, no breeze can get in.

390
00:21:30,440 --> 00:21:31,040
By the way.

391
00:21:31,440 --> 00:21:34,500
You all have air conditioners in your dorms now, right?

392
00:21:34,600 --> 00:21:36,200
In our time, let alone air conditioners,

393
00:21:36,200 --> 00:21:37,720
even the electric fans didn't work well.

394
00:21:37,720 --> 00:21:38,450
It was so hot.

395
00:21:38,480 --> 00:21:39,240
What did it end up like?

396
00:21:39,240 --> 00:21:40,440
As soon as you pushed the door open,

397
00:21:40,440 --> 00:21:42,200
it looked like an erotic painting.

398
00:21:42,200 --> 00:21:44,000
All the men were naked.

399
00:21:44,800 --> 00:21:46,200
Of course, we wore pants.

400
00:21:46,360 --> 00:21:47,160
Do you know what happened

401
00:21:47,160 --> 00:21:48,820
in the end because of the heat?

402
00:21:49,040 --> 00:21:50,280
Your whole dorm went

403
00:21:50,800 --> 00:21:51,800
and booked a room.

404
00:21:54,080 --> 00:21:55,280
Have I told you this before?

405
00:21:55,280 --> 00:21:56,810
You've mentioned it twice.

406
00:22:01,400 --> 00:22:03,120
But I haven't told Xiao Cen about it.

407
00:22:03,120 --> 00:22:04,160
Xiao Cen, did you know?

408
00:22:04,160 --> 00:22:05,520
It was so hot that the five of us guys

409
00:22:05,520 --> 00:22:06,780
went to get a hotel room

410
00:22:06,960 --> 00:22:08,520
and squeezed into one standard room.

411
00:22:08,520 --> 00:22:09,240
Could we even fit?

412
00:22:09,240 --> 00:22:10,500
We couldn't fit at all.

413
00:22:10,600 --> 00:22:11,960
In the end, I slept in the bathtub.

414
00:22:11,960 --> 00:22:13,400
And then I developed a condition.

415
00:22:13,400 --> 00:22:15,400
I must have a bathtub when buying a house.

416
00:22:15,400 --> 00:22:18,330
Otherwise, I always feel the space isn't big enough.

417
00:22:24,520 --> 00:22:27,320
I didn't expect the boss to talk for so long.

418
00:22:27,840 --> 00:22:28,600
Maybe he

419
00:22:29,520 --> 00:22:31,250
occasionally feels bored too.

420
00:22:33,440 --> 00:22:34,440
He told me before.

421
00:22:35,480 --> 00:22:37,810
He has been in Jingdezhen for seven years.

422
00:22:39,560 --> 00:22:41,760
It seems his business used to be quite large.

423
00:22:41,760 --> 00:22:43,220
Then he suddenly got sick.

424
00:22:43,480 --> 00:22:44,720
Those close to him

425
00:22:44,880 --> 00:22:46,540
gradually left him one by one.

426
00:22:48,200 --> 00:22:49,330
After he recovered,

427
00:22:50,400 --> 00:22:51,930
he left everything behind,

428
00:22:52,880 --> 00:22:53,480
came here,

429
00:22:54,280 --> 00:22:55,480
and opened this shop.

430
00:22:58,040 --> 00:22:59,700
Maybe everyone who comes here

431
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:02,480
has their own past.

432
00:23:10,080 --> 00:23:10,640
You know,

433
00:23:11,040 --> 00:23:12,680
we have a tradition here in Jingdezhen

434
00:23:12,680 --> 00:23:14,000
that has lasted for thousands of years.

435
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:15,660
It's reusing old kiln bricks.

436
00:23:15,840 --> 00:23:16,840
Because a traditional wood kiln,

437
00:23:16,840 --> 00:23:19,040
after firing porcelain about 80 times,

438
00:23:19,280 --> 00:23:20,480
the bricks used to build it

439
00:23:20,480 --> 00:23:22,800
will reach their life cycle

440
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:25,260
and naturally be replaced from the kiln.

441
00:23:25,720 --> 00:23:28,360
Then these old kiln bricks covered in kiln sweat

442
00:23:28,360 --> 00:23:30,080
are combined with new ones

443
00:23:30,200 --> 00:23:32,800
and become building materials for the locals.

444
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:34,080
I see.

445
00:23:34,440 --> 00:23:37,040
The Imperial Kiln is the origin of Jingdezhen.

446
00:23:37,080 --> 00:23:38,040
But I think

447
00:23:38,280 --> 00:23:40,200
it preserves the memory

448
00:23:40,200 --> 00:23:41,880
and warmth of this city even more.

449
00:23:41,880 --> 00:23:44,040
Every time I visit and walk around here,

450
00:23:44,040 --> 00:23:45,760
it feels like I can travel through time.

451
00:23:45,760 --> 00:23:47,000
It's like I can really see the ancients

452
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:48,360
working hard here.

453
00:23:49,600 --> 00:23:50,600
The ones displayed in this row

454
00:23:50,600 --> 00:23:52,260
are all modern ceramic works.

455
00:24:06,040 --> 00:24:06,640
Look.

456
00:24:07,080 --> 00:24:09,210
This one is Three Rams Bringing Bliss.

457
00:24:09,880 --> 00:24:10,760
So beautiful.

458
00:24:13,720 --> 00:24:14,320
By the way,

459
00:24:14,920 --> 00:24:16,280
can I ask you a favor?

460
00:24:16,880 --> 00:24:17,560
What is it?

461
00:24:17,960 --> 00:24:19,120
If you're free,

462
00:24:19,400 --> 00:24:21,080
can you take me to your school's museum

463
00:24:21,080 --> 00:24:21,920
for a visit?

464
00:24:22,800 --> 00:24:24,280
Our school's museum?

465
00:24:24,600 --> 00:24:25,000
Yes.

466
00:24:25,560 --> 00:24:26,640
Your school's museum

467
00:24:26,640 --> 00:24:27,880
has many rare collections.

468
00:24:27,880 --> 00:24:29,610
I've always wanted to see them.

469
00:24:31,640 --> 00:24:33,320
Because only people from your school can make a reservation,

470
00:24:33,320 --> 00:24:34,080
so...

471
00:24:35,080 --> 00:24:35,410
Okay.

472
00:24:36,200 --> 00:24:36,800
Thank you.

473
00:24:36,960 --> 00:24:38,000
No problem. Let's go.
